{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_122","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented FW-M14-004 in the dashboard stack.\n\nThe main change is a new scene/circuit normalization layer in [dashboard_scene_circuit.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/dashboard_scene_circuit.py), wired into [dashboard_session_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/dashboard_session_planning.py). The scene payload now carries renderable replay frames derived from the packaged stimulus or retinal contracts, with clear fallback/unavailable handling. The circuit payload now includes selected-root metadata, one-hop connectivity context, edge summaries, and explicit linked click/hover payloads grounded in the existing geometry, selection, and coupling assets.\n\nI also upgraded the offline shell in [dashboard_shell.js](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/dashboard_assets/dashboard_shell.js), [dashboard_shell.css](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/dashboard_assets/dashboard_shell.css), and [dashboard_app_shell.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/dashboard_app_shell.py) so the scene pane renders synchronized frames from the packaged session payload and the circuit pane renders a linked graph/roster/metadata view with shared hover and selection state. Companion coverage was added in [test_dashboard_scene_circuit.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_dashboard_scene_circuit.py), and the rationale note is at [FW-M14-004_rationale.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/ui_dashboard_notes/FW-M14-004_rationale.md).\n\nVerified with:\n- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_dashboard_scene_circuit t